---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Home"
  description="Agency, Process, Scale — a structured knowledge system for the APS Framework."
>
  <div class="content-wrapper">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Agency &middot; Process &middot; Scale</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        A structured knowledge system for the APS Framework &mdash; integrating canonical definitions,
        conceptual articles, and research streams into a unified account of life as
        viability-oriented, constraint-closed organisation.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a href="/orientation/what-is-aps/" class="btn btn-primary">Read: What Is APS?</a>
        <a href="/glossary/" class="btn btn-secondary">Explore the Glossary</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Start Here -->
    <section class="home-section where-to-begin">
      <h2>Start Here</h2>
      <p>
        The APS Framework is a connected conceptual system. These entry points provide
        different ways to engage with it.
      </p>
      <div class="begin-grid">
        <div class="begin-group">
          <h3>New to APS</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/orientation/what-is-aps/">What Is APS? &mdash; A One-Page Framework Overview</a></li>
            <li><a href="/articles/what-is-life/">What Is Life? &mdash; A Biological Question Revisited</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="begin-group">
          <h3>Understand the Concepts</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/orientation/aps-glossary/">The APS Glossary &mdash; Why Definitions Matter</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="begin-group">
          <h3>Explore the Framework</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/articles/biology/">Biology &mdash; What the Science of Life Explains</a></li>
            <li><a href="/orientation/understanding-aps/">Understanding APS &mdash; The Structure of the Framework</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="begin-group">
          <h3>How to Navigate</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/orientation/how-to-read/">How to Read APS</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="begin-note">
        APS concepts are interdependent and should be read as part of a constraint-closed conceptual system.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Clusters -->
    <section class="home-section">
      <h2>Knowledge Clusters</h2>
      <p>
        The APS Framework is organised into flat, non-hierarchical clusters. Each cluster groups
        related articles, glossary entries, and research streams within a unified explanatory grammar.
      </p>
      <div class="cluster-grid">
        <a href="/clusters/foundations/" class="cluster-card">
          <h3>Foundations of the APS Framework</h3>
          <p>Core definitions, principles, and the formal structure of Agency, Process, and Scale.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clusters/definition-borderlines/" class="cluster-card">
          <h3>Definition &amp; Borderlines</h3>
          <p>
            Conceptual boundaries, distinctions, and relations to adjacent frameworks.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clusters/cognition-mind/" class="cluster-card">
          <h3>Cognition &amp; Mind</h3>
          <p>
            APS accounts of cognition, including 4E approaches, enactivism, and non-neural systems.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clusters/empirical-interface/" class="cluster-card">
          <h3>Empirical Interface</h3>
          <p>
            Operationalisation, measurement strategies, and empirical test cases.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clusters/scaling-complexity/" class="cluster-card">
          <h3>Scaling &amp; Complexity</h3>
          <p>
            Multi-scale organisation, emergence, and cross-scale integration.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clusters/historical-context/" class="cluster-card">
          <h3>Historical &amp; Philosophical Context</h3>
          <p>
            Intellectual foundations, including Aristotle, process philosophy, and systems theory.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/clusters/conceptual-foundations/" class="cluster-card">
          <h3>Conceptual Foundations &amp; Explanatory Grammar</h3>
          <p>
            The structure of explanation in APS &mdash; what counts as a valid concept and a well-formed claim.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Recent Publications -->
    <section class="home-section">
      <h2>Recent Canonical Publications</h2>
      <ul class="card-list">
        <li class="card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              <a href="/articles/scale-time-persistence/">Scale, Time, and Persistence</a>
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-canonical">Canonical</span>
            <span class="badge badge-type badge-article">Article</span>
          </div>
          <p class="card-excerpt">
            An analysis of how scale operates as a structural condition for processual persistence,
            distinguishing APS from flat-ontology approaches.
          </p>
          <div class="card-meta">Cluster: Foundations &middot; Revised: 2026-02-01</div>
        </li>
        <li class="card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/glossary/function/">Function (Glossary)</a></h3>
            <span class="badge badge-canonical">Canonical</span>
            <span class="badge badge-type badge-glossary">Glossary</span>
          </div>
          <p class="card-excerpt">
            A canonical definition of "function" within the APS framework, clarifying its relation
            to biological and philosophical usage.
          </p>
          <div class="card-meta">
            Cluster: Definition &amp; Borderlines &middot; Revised: 2026-02-01
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              <a href="/articles/agency-without-intentions/">Agency Without Intentions</a>
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-evolving">Evolving</span>
            <span class="badge badge-type badge-article">Article</span>
          </div>
          <p class="card-excerpt">
            Exploring how APS conceptualises agency in systems that lack intentional states &mdash;
            from bacterial chemotaxis to institutional behaviour.
          </p>
          <div class="card-meta">Cluster: Cognition &amp; Mind &middot; Revised: 2026-02-15</div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
